The paper deals with image classification and proposes a neural network architecture that can handle variations in images such as affine transformations and shape distortions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel neural network architecture, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions cross dataset classification tasks and few-shot learning problems, which suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) datasets such as MNIST and CIFAR-10, which suggests that it could also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
